\title{the substitution unit of a representable map}
\author{jonmsterling}
\date{2023-11-07}
\taxon{definition}

\import{jms-00DJ}


\let\C{#{\mathcal{C}}}

\p{Let \Mor{p}{E}{U} be a representable map in #{\Psh\C}, so that \Mor{q}{\CatEl{U}}{\CatEl{E}} is the corresponding [generic elements functor](jms-00DL). We may define a natural transformation \Mor{\eta}{\Idn{\CatEl{E}}}{q\circ\CatEl{p}} that we shall call the \em{substitution unit} of the representable map \Mor{p}{E}{U}.}

\p{We define \Mor{\eta}{\Idn{\CatEl{E}}}{q\circ\CatEl{p}} assigning to each #{\Gamma\vdash a : A} the upper-hand depicted below:}

\texfig{
  \begin{tikzpicture}[diagram]
    \SpliceDiagramSquare<sq/>{
      nw/style = pullback,
      nw = \Gamma.A,
      sw = \Gamma,
      ne = E,
      se = U,
      east = p,
      north = qA,
      south = {A},
      north/style = {thick, ->},
      north/node/style = upright desc,
    }
    \node[above left = of sq/nw,xshift=-.5cm] (nw) {$\Gamma$};
    \draw[->,thick,bend left=30] (nw) to node[sloped,above] (a) {$a$} (sq/ne);
    \draw[double,bend right=30] (nw) to (sq/sw);
    \draw[->,exists,thick] (nw) to node[desc] {$\gl{\Gamma,a}$} (sq/nw);
    \node[between = sq/nw and a] {${\Downarrow} \eta_a$};
  \end{tikzpicture}
}

\p{The reason to refer to \Mor{\eta}{\Idn{\CatEl{E}}}{q\circ\CatEl{p}} as the \em{substitution unit} is that it witnesses the fact that \em{every} element of a given type arises from that typeâ€™s generic element by substitution.}
